# About Me

## Background

I am a third-year Computer Science student specializing in Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning at VIT-AP University. My journey into tech began with a curiosity for how data can drive decision-making, which led me to explore the depths of Python, Java, and C++. I have maintained a CGPA of 7.91/10.00 while balancing rigorous coursework with hands-on project development.

## What I Do

As an AI Engineer, I focus on building end-to-end machine learning solutions. From developing predictive models for sports analytics using XGBoost to implementing NLP pipelines for fraud detection, I enjoy turning raw data into actionable insights. I am particularly passionate about understanding the mathematical foundations of deep learning, which drove me to build neural networks from scratch using only NumPy.

## My Approach

I believe in a "first-principles" approach to engineering. Whether it's solving algorithmic problems on LeetCode or architecting a feature engineering pipeline, I prioritize understanding the core mechanics before applying high-level abstractions. I value clean, modular code and robust data preprocessing as the backbone of any successful AI project.

## Outside of Work

When I'm not training models or debugging code, I enjoy solving complex algorithmic challenges on platforms like HackerRank and LeetCode, where I've solved over 150 problems. I am also an avid follower of the latest advancements in Generative AI and Computer Vision.

